questions.question:
Consider the following languages:
- L1 = {ww | w in {a,b}*}
- L2 = {ww^R | w in {a,b}*, w^R is the reverse of w}
- L3 = {0^(2i) | i is an integer}
- L4 = {0^(i^2) | i is an integer}

Which of the languages are regular?

A. Only L1 and L2
B. Only L2, L3 and L4
C. Only L3 and L4
D. Only L3

If s is a string over {a, b}* then let n_a(s) denote the number of a's in s and n_b(s) denote the number of b's in s. Which one of the following languages is NOT regular?

A. L = {s in {a,b}* | n_a(s) is a 3-digit prime}
B. L = {s in {a,b}* | for every prefix s' of s, |n_a(s') - n_b(s')| <= 2}
C. L = {s in {a,b}* | n_a(s) - n_b(s) <= 4}
D. L = {s in {a,b}* | n_a(s) mod 5 = 0}

Which of the following languages is regular?

A. {ww^R | w in {0,1}*}
B. {ww^R x | x,w in {0,1}*}
C. {wxw^R | w,x in {0,1}*, |w| = |x|}
D. {xww^R | x,w in {0,1}*, |x| = |w|}
